      <!-- ============ GO STUDY IT YOURSELF ============ -->
      <section class="study-body">
        <h2>Go Study It Yourself</h2>

        <p class="drop-cap">
          Don&rsquo;t take our word for it. Every claim can be verified with free tools:
        </p>

        <div class="cross-ref-box">
          <h4>Look Up Any Greek or Hebrew Word</h4>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="https://www.blueletterbible.org" class="verse-ref">Blue Letter Bible</a> &mdash; <span class="ref-text">Search any verse, click any word for Greek/Hebrew and Strong&rsquo;s number. Look up <a href="../lexicon/h7854.html" style="color:var(--ultramarine);text-decoration:none;">H7854</a> (<em>satan</em>), <a href="../lexicon/h1966.html" style="color:var(--ultramarine);text-decoration:none;">H1966</a> (<em>helel</em>), <a href="../lexicon/g1228.html" style="color:var(--ultramarine);text-decoration:none;">G1228</a> (<em>diabolos</em>).</span></li>
            <li><a href="https://biblehub.com/interlinear/" class="verse-ref">Bible Hub Interlinear</a> &mdash; <span class="ref-text">Word-by-word original languages. Check Isaiah 14:12 and Ezekiel 28:12 yourself.</span></li>
            <li><a href="https://www.stepbible.org" class="verse-ref">STEP Bible (Tyndale House)</a> &mdash; <span class="ref-text">Advanced morphology and cross-references.</span></li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="cross-ref-box">
          <h4>Compare Translations &bull; Read the Fathers &bull; Learn the Languages</h4>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="https://www.biblegateway.com" class="verse-ref">Bible Gateway</a> &mdash; <span class="ref-text">Compare Isaiah 14:12 across 60+ translations. See who keeps &ldquo;Lucifer&rdquo; and who doesn&rsquo;t.</span></li>
            <li><a href="https://www.newadvent.org/fathers/" class="verse-ref">New Advent: Church Fathers</a> &mdash; <span class="ref-text">Read what Origen, Tertullian, and Augustine actually wrote about the adversary.</span></li>
            <li><a href="https://www.billmounce.com/greek-dictionary" class="verse-ref">Bill Mounce&rsquo;s Greek Resources</a> &mdash; <span class="ref-text">Free Greek dictionary.</span></li>
            <li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/@AlephwithBeth" class="verse-ref">Aleph with Beth (YouTube)</a> &mdash; <span class="ref-text">Free Biblical Hebrew lessons.</span></li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <p>
          <strong>The rule:</strong> never believe something about the Bible just because someone told you&mdash;including us. Open the Hebrew. Open the Greek. Check every verse in context.
        </p>

        <blockquote class="scripture-quote">
          These were more fair-minded than those in Thessalonica, in that they received the word with all readiness, and <strong>searched the Scriptures daily</strong> to find out whether these things were so.
          <cite class="scripture-ref">&mdash; Acts 17:11</cite>
        </blockquote>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider">

